Bootstrap
---------
1. Bootstrap is an HTML, CSS and Javascript framework, which is mainly used to make web pages responsive.
2. Bootstrap is an open source, which means it can be downloaded free of cost from the internet.
3. Bootstrap provides consistent design.
4. Bootstrap is compatible with almost all modern web browsers
5. Bootstrap internally uses media query.
6. Bootstrap works on the concept of classes.
7. There are several versions of bootstrap, and out of which 
   Bootstrap 5 is the latest.
8. Bootstrap works on grid system.
9. We can also use CDN path to implement bootstrap without downloading it.